{"cursor":"8437","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Former Country\n| native_name = Bonoman common_name = Bonoman continent = Africa region = West\n| Africa country = Ghana event_start = year_start = 11th century date_start =\n| event_end = Dissolved event4 = Incorporation into Ghana year_end = 19th\n| century date_event4 = 1957 p1 = image_p1 = s1 = Ashanti Empire flag_s1 =\n| Flag_of_Ashanti.svg capital = Begho common_languages = Akan languages\n| religion = Ancestor worship government_type = Monarchy leader1 = year_leader1\n| = leader2 = }}\n\n'Bonoman' (Bono State) was a trading state created by the Abron people. Bonoman\nwas a medieval Akan kingdom in what is now the Brong-Ahafo Region of Ghana and\neastern Ivory Coast. It is generally accepted as the origin of the subgroups of\nthe Akan people who migrated out of the state at various times to create new\nAkan states in search of gold. The gold trade, which started to boom in Bonoman\nas early in the 12th century, was the genesis of Akan power and wealth in the\nregion, beginning in the Middle Ages.\n","linknr":181,"url":"Bonoman","recorded":1375055999,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Bonoman&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Bonoman&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//me